<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1400 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> ["Republican Decree No. 1" on the formation of the </F>
<ORGANIZATION>Democratic Republic of Yemen Council of Ministers</ORGANIZATION> issued in <LOCATION>Aden</LOCATION> 
on 1 <DATE>June</DATE>] 
  [Text] In the name of God, the merciful and compassionate, 
Democratic Republic of <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION> [DRY], the chairman of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION>, having consulted the interim Constitution 
of the DRY and the decree of the Presidential Council No. 3 of 
<DATE>1994</DATE>, charging brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas with the task 
of forming the government and following the approval of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION>, has decreed: 
<H5>  Article 1: The <ORGANIZATION>Council of Ministers</ORGANIZATION> shall be formed in the </H5>
following manner: 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Prime Minister and Finance Minister:  |Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas             | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Deputy Prime Minister:                |<PERSON>Muhammad Haydarah Masdus</PERSON>              | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of |Muhsin Muhammad Bin Abu-Bakr Bin-Farid| 
|Planning and Development:             |                                      | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Deputy Prime Minister and <ORGANIZATION>Minister of |Salih Ubayd Ahmad                     | 
|Transport</ORGANIZATION> and Communications:         |                                      | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Min-|'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj      | 
