<H3> <TI>   Saddam Assumes Prime Minister's Position </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Assumes Prime Minister's Position </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2905180994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1748 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2905180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Baghdad</LOCATION>, 29 <DATE>May</DATE> (INA)--In a statement issued <DATE>today</DATE>, 
the <ORGANIZATION>Revolution Command Council</ORGANIZATION> [RCC] has decided that President 
<PERSON>Saddam Husayn</PERSON> shall directly assume the post of prime minister. 
His excellency accepted this nomination. 
  A presidential decree was issued relieving the prime 
minister, the deputy prime minister, and the ministers of their 
posts. 
  Another presidential decree was issued forming a Cabinet 
under President <PERSON>Saddam Husayn</PERSON>. Three deputy prime ministers 
were appointed. Ministers were also named for various 
portfolios. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>RCC</ORGANIZATION> statement says: 
  In view of the circumstances of the unjust blockade and the 
need for exceptional interest in economic issues and the 
citizens' lives and in order to reinforce the heroic 
steadfastness of our great people and the achievements of that 
steadfastness, which constitute a basic factor in our successful 
struggle, God willing, to lift the unjust blockade, and in 
accordance with the provisions of Paragraph C of Article 61 of 
the Constitution, the <ORGANIZATION>RCC</ORGANIZATION>, during its session on 18 Dhu 
al-Hijjah <DATE>1414</DATE> <ORGANIZATION>Hegira</ORGANIZATION>, corresponding to 29 <DATE>May 1994</DATE>, has decided 
that President <PERSON>Saddam Husayn</PERSON> shall directly assume the post of 
prime minister. His excellency agreed to this nomination for 
the reasons and circumstances presented by the council. 
  The presidential decree forming the new <ORGANIZATION>Council of 
Ministers</ORGANIZATION> reads: 
  Taking cognizance of the provisions of Paragraphs C and D of 
Article 58 of the Constitution, we decree the following: 
  First, <ORGANIZATION>The Council of Ministers</ORGANIZATION> will be formed under our 
chairmanship; 
  Second, Vice President <PERSON>Taha Yasin Ramadan</PERSON> shall be appointed 
deputy prime minister; 
  Third, <LOCATION>Tariq</LOCATION> 'Aziz shall be appointed deputy prime minister; 
  Fourth, <PERSON>Muhammad Hamzah</PERSON> al-Zubaydi shall be appointed deputy 
prime minister; 
  Fifth, the following persons shall be appointed to the 
ministerial posts indicated alongside their names: 
  1. Staff General '<PERSON>Ali Hasan al-Majid</PERSON>, defense minister. 
  2. Ahmad <PERSON>Husayn Khudayyir</PERSON>, finance minister. 
  3. <PERSON>Latif Nusayyif Jasim</PERSON>, labor and social affairs 
minister. 
  4. Arshad Muhammad Ahmad al-Zibari, state minister. 
  5. Samal <PERSON>Majid Faraj</PERSON>, planning minister. 
  6. Staff General 'Abd-al-Jabbar <PERSON>Khalil Shanshal</PERSON>, minister 
of state for military affairs. 
  7. Muhammad <PERSON>Mahdi Salih</PERSON>, trade minister. 
  8. Staff General <PERSON>Husayn Kamil Hasan</PERSON>, industry and 
minerals minister. 
  9. Umid <PERSON>Midhat Mubarak</PERSON>, health minister. 
  10. <PERSON>Karim Hasan Rida</PERSON>, agriculture minister. 
  11. Muhammad Sa'id <PERSON>Kazim al-Sahhaf</PERSON>, foreign minister. 
  12. Hamid <PERSON>Yusuf Hammadi</PERSON>, culture and information minister. 
  13. Shabib Lazim al-Maliki, justice minister. 
  14. Hikmat 'Abdallah al-Bazzaz, education minister. 
  15. Mahmud Dhiyab al-Ahmad, housing and construction 
minister. 
  16. Watban Ibrahim al-Hasan, interior minister. 
  17. Humam 'Abd-al-Khaliq 'Abd-al-Ghafur, higher education 
and scientific research minister. 
  18. Nizar Jum'ah al-Qasir, irrigation minister. 
  19. Safa' <PERSON>Hadi Jawad</PERSON>, oil minister. 
  20. Ahmad <PERSON>Murtada Ahmad Khalil</PERSON>, transport and 
telecommunications minister. 
  21. 'Abd-al-Mun'im <PERSON>Ahmad Salih</PERSON>, awqaf and religious 
affairs minister. 
  22. 'Abd-al-Wahhab '<PERSON>Umar Mirza al-Atrushi</PERSON>, state minister. 
  The prime minister and ministers shall implement this 
decree. 
  Written in <LOCATION>Baghdad</LOCATION> on 18 Dhu al-Hijjah, <DATE>1414</DATE> hegira, 
corresponding to 29 <DATE>May 1994</DATE>. 
  [Signed] <PERSON>Saddam Husayn</PERSON>, president of the Republic 

</TEXT>

