<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad Greets Yemeni President Upon Arrival </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Asad, Salih Discuss Issues </H4>
<F P=102> JN2403210794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2403210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The brothers President 'Ali '<PERSON>Abdallah Salih</PERSON>, 
chairman of the [<ORGANIZATION>Yemeni] Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION>, and Syrian 
President <PERSON>Hafiz</PERSON> al-Asad held a closed meeting at the <ORGANIZATION>People's 
Palace</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Damascus</LOCATION> <TIME>this evening</TIME>. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Yemeni News Agency</ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION>SABA</ORGANIZATION>' has learned that the talks 
addressed the strong fraternal bilateral ties, the means of 
promoting them, issues of common interest to the two fraternal 
countries, and Arab issues. 
  The brother <ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION> chairman briefed his 
brother 
His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad on developments in our 
country in light of the accord document and the efforts made to 
contain the crisis and ensure the convening of meetings by the 
Constitutional institutions to help implement the accord 
document. 
  The session of Yemeni-Syrian talks was held at the People's 
Palace at <DATE>1730</DATE>, <LOCATION>Damascus</LOCATION> time, today. The talks were cochaired 
by brothers Lieutenant General '<PERSON>Ali 'Abdallah Salih</PERSON>, chairman of 
the <ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION>, and His Excellency President <PERSON>Hafiz</PERSON> 
al-Asad of the <ORGANIZATION>Syrian Arab Republic</ORGANIZATION>. 
  During this session of talks, the two leaders reviewed 
current Arab developments and issues of interest to our Arab 
nation, foremost among which are developments in the Palestine 
question and the efforts under way to achieve a just and 
comprehensive peace in the region on the basis of regaining Arab 
rights. 
  The two leaders stressed the need to promote efforts to 
clear 
the Arab atmosphere and restore Arab solidarity so Arabs can 
cope with the enormous challenges facing our Arab nation, and so 
just, comprehensive, and durable peace can be achieved in the 
region. Issues pertaining to the fraternal bilateral ties were 
also addressed. 
  His Excellency President <PERSON>Hafiz</PERSON> al-Asad of the <ORGANIZATION>Syrian Arab 
Republic</ORGANIZATION> has reiterated <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>'s support for our people, and for 
our country's stability. He also emphasized that <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION> supports 
all efforts to safeguard Yemeni unity and enhance its march, 
given that Yemeni unity is a significant pan-Arab accomplishment 
along the path of Arab unity, and a gain that is dear to all 
Arabs. He asserted that <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION>'s security, stability, and safety 
concern <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION> and all the sons of the Arab nation, given that 
the pan-Arab security is an indivisible whole. 
  For his part, the brother president expressed his 
appreciation of the fraternal efforts and stands of the 
fraternal Syrians, as manifested in their support for the march 
of unity and democracy in our country. He indicated that the 
Yemeni-Syrian ties are fraternal and strong. 
  At the outset of this session of talks, His Excellency 
President Hafiz al-Asad welcomed the brother <ORGANIZATION>Presidential 
Council</ORGANIZATION> chairman and the delegation accompanying him on this 
visit. He noted the strong and deep fraternal ties binding the 
two fraternal peoples. He expressed his confidence that this 
visit will reinforce these strong ties in the interest of the 
two fraternal peoples and the Arab nation. 
  This session of talks was attended for <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION> by Deputy Prime 
Minister 'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Anisi, <ORGANIZATION>Minister of Planning and 
Development Dr.</ORGANIZATION> 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, Foreign Affairs 
Minister <PERSON>Muhammad Salim Basindwah</PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council Office</ORGANIZATION> 
Chief 'Ali Muhammad al-Anisi, and Yemeni Ambassador to <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION> 
Muhammad Shutfah. For <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>, the talks were attended by Vice 
President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi, 
Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', and <ORGANIZATION>Minister of State for 
Foreign Affairs Nasir Qaddur</ORGANIZATION>. 

</TEXT>

