<F P=103> JN1005141894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Shaykh '<PERSON>Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar</PERSON>, 
speaker of the <ORGANIZATION>House of Representatives</ORGANIZATION>, and Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani, minister of planning and development, left <LOCATION>Sanaa 
International Airport</LOCATION> for the Kingdom of <LOCATION>Saudi Arabia</LOCATION> <TIME>this 
afternoon</TIME>. They are carrying a message from brother Lieutenant 
General 'Ali '<PERSON>Abdallah Salih</PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION>Presidential 
Council</ORGANIZATION>, to his brother King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-<PERSON>'Aziz</PERSON>, custodian 
of the two holy mosques. It deals with the current developments 
in our country and issues of concern to the two sisterly 
countries. 
  Foreign Minister <PERSON>Muhammad Salim Basindwah</PERSON> also left <LOCATION>Sanaa</LOCATION> 
airport for <LOCATION>Cairo</LOCATION> with a message from brother Lt. Gen. 'Ali 
'<PERSON>Abdallah Salih</PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION>Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION>, to his 
brother President <PERSON>Muhammad Husni Mubarak</PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION>Arab 
Republic of Egypt</ORGANIZATION>. 

</TEXT>

