  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received <PERSON>Salim Salih 
Muhammad</PERSON>, member of the <ORGANIZATION>Yemeni Presidential Council</ORGANIZATION> and 
assistant secretary general of the <ORGANIZATION>Yemeni Socialist Party</ORGANIZATION> [YSP], 
and Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dali, member of the <ORGANIZATION>YSP Political 
Bureau</ORGANIZATION>, at <DATE>1300 today</DATE>. The meeting was attended by <PERSON>Rashid 
Akhtarini</PERSON>, deputy prime minister for services affairs, and 
Muhammad 'Abduh Shatfah, Yemeni Ambassador in <LOCATION>Damascus</LOCATION>. 
  Talks dealt with the Yemeni situation and its complications. 
The president stressed the pan-Arab importance of safeguarding 
<LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION>'s unity and the need to resolve the existing differences 
and complications through dialogue. 
  <PERSON>Salim Salih Muhammad</PERSON> and the accompanying delegation left 
<LOCATION>Damascus</LOCATION> this afternoon following a three-day visit to <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>. 
He was seen off at <LOCATION>Damascus International Airport</LOCATION> by <PERSON>Rashid 
Akhtarini</PERSON>, deputy prime minister for services affairs; Muhammad 
'<PERSON>Abduh Shatfah</PERSON>, the Yemeni ambassador in <LOCATION>Damascus</LOCATION>; and the 
<ORGANIZATION>Yemeni Embassy</ORGANIZATION> staff. 
  Muhammad made a statement to a SANA [<ORGANIZATION>Syrian Arab News 
Agency</ORGANIZATION>] 
correspondent, noting: <DATE>Today</DATE>, we had the honor of meeting with 
His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad. We discussed the 
current situation in <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION> and the efforts being made to 
circumvent the existing crisis and safeguard <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION>'s unity. 
  He lauded <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>'s pan-Arab positions on Arab issues under 
the 
leadership of President Hafiz al-Asad, as well as <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>'s 
pioneering role in supporting the unity of Arab ranks and 
achieving Arab solidarity. He said: We sensed from his 
excellency a great understanding of what is taking place in 
<LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION>, and his excellency stressed <LOCATION>Syria</LOCATION>'s interest in, and 
constant care for, <LOCATION>Yemen</LOCATION>'s unity. 

</TEXT>

